    <text id="R14613242T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Union Colonel H. B. Reed, commanding at Staunton, writes Confederate Colonel W.
                    P. Thompson in April, 1865, to inform him of surrender terms.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    HDQRS. U. S. FORCES,
                    <name type="recipient">Col. W. P. THOMPSON,<lb/> Cmdg. Jackson's Brigade,
                        Lomax's Division, &amp;c.:</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1865-04-30">April 30, 1865.</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton, Va.,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>COL.:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I have had the honor to receive at the hands of Capt. Silcott, with flag of
                    truce, a communication for you asking upon what terms you can surrender troops
                    under your command. I beg to say in reply, that the United States Government
                    will receive your command upon the same terms given to the Army of Northern
                    Virginia, viz, officers and men to give their parole of honor not to take up
                    arms against the United States until exchanged; all arms, horses, and public
                    property to be turned over to the United States, officers to retain their
                    side-arms, private horses, and personal baggage.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>I have the honor to remain, colonel, very respectfully, your obedient
                        servant,</salute>
                    <signed>H. B. REED,<lb/> Col., Twenty-second New York Cav., Cmdg. U. S. Forces
                        at Staunton.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
